Small Assignment:
git status 
    - this command tells us the state of the repository and where we are staged.

rm -rf ./Sample 
    - the rm command removes a file. -rf is an option that will allow you to force a removal from the root. ./Sample is the file to be removed. 

/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
    - this is the curl command. it allows you to transfer data. This command is installing Homebrew onto your computer.

